Unwrap a single table dm

Source: R/dm_wrap.R
dm_unwrap.Rd

dm_unwrap() unwraps all tables in a dm object so that the resulting dm matches a given ptype dm. It runs a sequence of dm_unnest_tbl() and dm_unpack_tbl() operations on the dm.

dm_unwrap(dm, ptype)

Arguments

dm

A dm.

ptype

A dm, only used to query names of primary and foreign keys.

Value

A dm.

See also

dm_wrap(), dm_unnest_tbl(), dm_examine_constraints(), dm_examine_cardinalities(), dm_ptype().

Examples


roundtrip <-
  dm_nycflights13() %>%
  dm_wrap(root = flights) %>%
  dm_unwrap(ptype = dm_ptype(dm_nycflights13()))
roundtrip
#> ── Metadata ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Tables: `flights`, `airlines`, `airports`, `planes`, `weather`
#> Columns: 53
#> Primary keys: 4
#> Foreign keys: 4

# The roundtrip has the same structure but fewer rows:
dm_nrow(dm_nycflights13())
#> airlines airports  flights   planes  weather 
#>       15       86     1761      945      144 
dm_nrow(roundtrip)
#>  flights airlines airports   planes  weather 
#>     1761       15        3     1112      105
